    "Maps of cognitive and social systems are normally connected hence the number of components is expected to be 1.",
    "They are smallto medium-sized hence we do not expect significant variations in distributions at the element-level, unlike e.g.",
    "degree distributions in large-scale networks.",
    "The most important nodes are often a reflection of the elicitation process, e.g.",
    "if the conversation starts with 'obesity' then it is likely that obesity will be at the center of the system."
